On Sun, Jan 30, 2000 at 12:58:19AM +0100, Jamie Lokier wrote:
> How much hardware can do _ISA_ scatter/gather DMA?
> 
> GFP_DMA is for ISA only.  The allocator changes are useful for folks
> doing 32 bit PCI DMA, but that's not the question that was asked here.
People have been using GFP_DMA / MAX_DMA_ADDRESS for other machines where
not the entire memory is usable for DMA for hardware or software reasons.
